<br>
Our Job is simple but important, we taunt and play meatshield, we try to take as much hits as possible, if we are down the Raid is in trouble or close to it, since we are the only ones who can take so many hits.<br>
<br>
When Big mobs are target of a raid we are the first to attack the beast and build up aggro, to make the beast beating only us, for this we need a cleric with good timing in our group, as well as backuphealers, to build up aggro we need good weapons, for us this means weapons with a low dly and decent damage, like a Lammy for example (9 dmg, 19 dly) with 1 Hand Weapons our taunt factor is at its best, the best weapons we can use for taunt have DoTs on them, nothing makes a mob more crazy at us as a fast weapon with a DoT, we also need a good haste item, to make sure that we can keep the mob on us when monks, rogues or rangers engage with their fast attacks. To survive this hits we need a high ac, as more as better. We don't really need much stats (beside Stamina which gives us HPs), AC is our most important stat we have.<br>
<br>
Also we are masters of all weapons, we can do critical hits with each weapons (critical hits are high dmg hits, well can be hehe).<br>
<br>
Additional to all this abilities we get disciplines, the best disciplines start at lvl 52, some last only some seconds, some last more, but all have a recharge time, starting from 15 minutes up to 60 minutes, even if we use a discipline we can't use another one until the recharge time is over.<br>
<br>
<b><u>Here is a list of our disciplines</u>:</b><br>
<br>
<b>Resistance (lvl 30)</b>: Increases the resists for 1 minutes, pre lvl 50 +5 to all resist, post 50 +10 to all resists, recharge time 60 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Fearless (lvl 40):</b> Increases the chance to resist a fear spell, not 100% immune, some dragon roars still go through, this discipline lasts 11 seconds, recharge time is 60 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Evasive (lvl 52):</b> The opponent will hit the warrior less often, but the warrior will also hit less often, duration is 3 minutes, recharge time is 15 minutes (this discpline is almost useless)<br>
<br>
<b>Charge (lvl 53):</b> With this disc our opponent cannot defend himself against us, each try to hit him is a hit, duration is 14 seconds, recharge time is 30 minutes.<br>
<br>
<b>Mighty Strike (lvl 54):</b> With this disc each hit will be a critical hit, cribbling blow in berserk frenzy, this is the best offensive discipline, my own record with this disc in berserk frenzy is almost 2000 dmg in 9 seconds, recharge time is 60 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Defensive (Lvl 55):</b> A better form of Evasive, but much better, duration again 3 minutes, recharge time is 15 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Furious (lvl 56):</b> Each attack of the opponent will be riposted by the warrior, this discipline is one of the keys to succeed against VS, duration is 9 seconds, recharge time is 60 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Precise (lvl 57):</b> Same like defensive or evasive but in the offensive way, warrior will hit more often but will get hit more often as well, duration is 3 minutes, recharge time is 30 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Fellstrike (lvl 58):</b> Offensive discipline, when used we do up to 4 times the base dmg of our weapons, duration is 12 seconds, recharge time is 30 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Fortitude (lvl 59):</b> Defensive disc, we are 100% immun to any melee dmg, duration is 8 seconds, recharge is 60 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Aggressive (lvl 60):</b> The warrior will do more damage with every blow landed but will also take more damage as well. Duration is 3 minutes, recharge time is 27 minutes.  <p>Zalbar The Mad
